          "reviewBody": "Recently I have visited this school for attending a chess tournament. There are few things which I would like to highlight regarding this school.\n1. The school is in an extreme interior place where transportation is definitely a thing on which people need to think repeatedly before visiting there.\n2. The school was arranging a tournament where more than two hundred students came to participate along with their parents ( elderly persons were also there to accompany their grandchildren) but the horrible school management didn't arrange any seating facility for anyone.\n3. I was there from 9am to 5pm without any chair literally sitting on the floor and no school officials were found to guide us regarding anything about the event. Few attendants were there who were only able to guide us about the dustbins.\n4. The projector was continuously showing the recording of their succesful students in board examinations ( both class X and XII) which was definitely an advertisement but with such horrible management and infrastructure the school needs to work hard before arranging such event.\n5. After a full day tournament, the school was not willing to provide any certificate for participation ( who scored below 3.5) which was also informed after waiting almost for another one hour. Yes I do agree that providing certificate was totally their own decision but if it was declared earlier then the tired students and parents didn't need to wait for long.\n6. Two more things I definitely want to request the school management are to maintain the scheduled time and a hygienic washroom. Both are equivalently important for everyone.",
